Stone built well, surrounded by loose stone blocks on a mounded area of soil

Masonry embankment for a distance of more than a mile and an elaborate system of underchannels connected with the tank at different points. Ruins of the Gond Palace on the embarkment
Stone built platform of uncertain date. Currently marked by late tomb

Brick lined well, possibly originally associated with the fort
Stone built well, with small water storage tank and parapet. Possibly Late Medieval

Older stone wall running up Ramtek hill alongside the modern steps from the village. This older wall runs parallel to and then under the modern steps. Potentially a part of the Medieval constructions in the area, leading up to the temple complex.
